Webapp.host_referral_216:
To participate as a mentor, you must 
- be a creator with access to the Go LIVE feature on TikTok; 
- have collected at least 20'000 Diamonds in the past 30 days; and
- and/or have received an invite to participate from TikTok (which will be sent only to selected creators).
Webapp.host_referral_217:
Mentors can collect rewards by inviting mentees to Go LIVE. 
Only users that meet the following criteria can be mentees:
- have registered an account on TikTok;
- have collected less than 250 Diamonds in the past 30 days.
Mentors will receive invite codes. Each code can be used to form a 30 days' mentorship, a mentee can only have 1 mentor. During the 30-days period, both you and mentees will collect rewards if the mentees complete the missions available to them. 
If a mentor invites users without access to the Go LIVE feature, these will get temporary access for 7 days once the mentorship is formed. These mentees may get granted permanent access to the Go LIVE feature after completing the Go LIVE mission within 7 days.

Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a1: {SO} refer to photos or other elements shown in a scene.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i1: Desktop capture: This source captures your entire desktop and is shown in LIVE Studio preview.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i2: Camera capture: When you turn on your camera, this source will capture the image from your camera and show in LIVE Studio preview.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i3: Photo source: You can add custom photos and see them in LIVE Studio preview.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i4: Video source: This type of source allows you to add custom videos to LIVE Studio preview.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i5: Goal source: This type of source allows you to add custom goals in your LIVE Studio preview, such as Gift goals and follower goals. They help your viewers understand your needs and interact with you.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i6: Reminder source: Reminder sources are added to LIVE Studio preview to notify you when your viewers follow you, subscribe, or send Gifts, and more.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q10_a2_i7: Countdown source: This adds a custom countdown timer to your LIVE Studio preview.

Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q11: How do I start my LIVE?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q11_a2: Once you confirm your LIVE information, you can start your LIVE.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q11_a2_i2: Set your LIVE title, cover photo, and topic to help your viewers find your LIVE more easily.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a1: Manage your sources and scenes on the panel to the left of your screen.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a1_i1: Click {AS} to add up to 10 sources, and you can define the shape and position of these sources to create personalized LIVE content.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a1_i2: Click {ASC} and set up different scenes. The settings of all scenes will be saved and you can switch to each scene at any time, even when you are LIVE.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a1_i3: Click {LS} to change between 16:9 and 9:16 so that you can have the best LIVE experience on your phone and your computer.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a2: The right-side panel shows your LIVE data and comments.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a2_i1: LIVE data is the statistics of your LIVE and shows the number of viewers and Gifts.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a2_i2: All viewer comments will appear in the LIVE chat.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a3: In the top section, you can set your content category, topics, and cover photo for your LIVE. All these settings can help your LIVE attract more potential viewers.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4: The bottom section is your control panel. It includes:
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4_i1: Record button: Once you start recording, a video copy will be saved to device.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4_i2: Mixer: You can control and adjust audio signals from different input sources.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4_i3: Microphone: You can turn it off or on anytime.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4_i4: Settings: All settings for software setup or your LIVE can be found here.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q12_a4_i5: Start: Start your LIVE when you are ready. Let's go LIVE!
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q13: How do I check comments and notifications?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q13_a1: You can see all comments and notifications on the panel on the main page.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q13_a2: Click a comment to reply or report the comment.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q13_a3: You can choose to show Gift notifications and comments, or turn it off in settings. You can also filter out comments that involve sensitive words that you choose.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q14: Where can I check how my LIVE looks?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q14_a1: You can go to http://TikTok.com/live to check your own LIVE and monitor how it looks.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q15: How do I view and share highlights from my LIVE?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q15_a1: After the end of your LIVE, the LIVE playback takes time to transcode, ranging from a few minutes to hours. After the transcoding is completed, you can watch and download the LIVE playback in LIVE Center.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q15_a2: Click your profile and you can find LIVE Center.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q16: What are the rules I should follow?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q16_a1: Once you choose to go LIVE with LIVE Studio, you should follow our {TOS}, {CG}, and other policies on TikTok. If your LIVE contains non-game related content, your access to LIVE Studio may be revoked.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q17: How do I report a problem?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q17_a1: If there is a problem with LIVE Studio, open the TikTok app and go to {Prof}. You can also give your feedback on our TikTok website.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q17_a2: Describe your problem in detail or give us screenshots of it.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q17_a3: Report an issue by sending us the log file. You can save the log file to your desktop by clicking {EL}.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q1_a1: TikTok LIVE Studio is the official LIVE tool for Windows users.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q2: Is TikTok LIVE Studio available for all creators?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q2_a1: This version of LIVE Studio is in internal testing and only available for some creators. The latest test started on May 5.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q3: How do I get access to TikTok LIVE Studio?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q3_a1: You can find the download page entrance on the profile list.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q3_a2: Download TikTok LIVE Studio (latest official version).
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q3_a3: Start LIVE Studio and log in to your TikTok account.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q4_a1: TikTok LIVE Studio only supports Windows at the moment.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q5: What's the difference between LIVE Studio and OBS?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q5_a1: TikTok LIVE Studio and OBS have similar functions. However, LIVE Studio is developed by TikTok. Creators can use it by logging in to TikTok. It also offers better information and content safety for creators.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q6: How do I set up LIVE Studio?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q6_a1: If you are not familiar with tools like TikTok LIVE Studio, click {SUN} and we will guide you through all the basic settings including setting up your camera, microphone, and publishing parameters. The details of the beginner guide can be found in the next section.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q6_a2: If you have other LIVE tools on your computer, click {IFATl} to migrate your settings on other tools to LIVE Studio. Alternatively, you can click {GLN} to enter the home page to set up your video source and layout.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q7: How do I set up LIVE Studio as a beginner？
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q7_a1: You can use the built-in microphone or your own external microphones. Make sure you test the audio level.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q7_a2: You can use the built-in camera or your own webcam.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q7_a3: The default video quality is 720p. You can adjust it to your LIVE preference.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8: What can I find on the LIVE Studio home page?
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a1_i1: You can customize up to 10 scenes at the same time. Each scene contains many sources.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a1_i2: Sources will be displayed in the middle of the canvas (area 2) after setup. You can edit the sources and adjust the position at any time.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a2_i1: To get more potential viewers, add your LIVE title, cover photo, and tags here.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a2_i2: You can choose whether to allow your viewers to send Gifts or comments during your LIVE.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a3_i1: Basic LIVE settings will be displayed such as the {GL} button, the {PL} button, or options to set up your camera, video, and microphone.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a3_i2: Click the mixer icon to access your audio settings. More settings such as the noise suppressor and audio channel management will be found there.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a3_i3: For video settings such as video quality, bitrate, green screen, and more, click the settings icon next to the {GL} button.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a4_i1: Real-time LIVE data will be displayed in this part during your LIVE. Your latest LIVE data will be there when you are not LIVE.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a4_i2: To view more details about your LIVE data, go to LIVE Center by clicking the icon at the top.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a5_i1: You can see all notifications here during your LIVE, including comments, Gifts, emojis, and more. View more details by clicking their nicknames.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a5_i2: If you want to block some words or phrases in your chat, go to settings and filter them out. Alternatively, you can just turn off {AC} or {AG}.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a5_i3: Click the pop-out icon and your chat box will become a transparent floating window. If you want to see comments while you are playing a full screen game on one single monitor, drag the window on your game screen to the side.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a6: LIVE Studio provides many tools for interactions, such as Treasure Box. You can find them all here.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q8_a7: The internet speed and SRU (system resource usage) will be displayed here.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q9_a1: {SC} are what viewers see on your shared screen. It includes elements like gaming content, webcam, and texts. You can build different setups for your scenes for a swift switch between different scenes. A scene is made of many sources.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q9_a2: {AAS}: Click {ASC} and rename the new scene.
Webapp.pm_ls_lsfaq_q9_a3: {LOPS}: select landscape or portrait scenes according to what you need.

Webapp.support_a_friend: Supporting a friend through body image or eating concerns
Webapp.support_a_friend_ed: If you have a friend struggling with these concerns, encourage them to contact a local eating disorder support group. When you talk to your friend, focus on the daily, non-eating disorder parts of their life, and avoid focusing on their eating disorder. Ask your friend open-ended questions, such as "how are you feeling today?", and listen to their answer without judging or interrupting, even if you don't agree with some of what they say. Be encouraging when your friend seems tired of the struggle to recover. Remind them of all the positive things about recovery, such as things that they used to like to do and will be able to do again once they are well. Discourage toxic and unhelpful talk by switching to more positive topics and remind them of their progress and wins, no matter how small.

Webapp.take_a_break_ed: Take a break when you need it
Webapp.take_a_break_ed_1: We live so much of our lives online and sometimes we may find ourselves drawing comparisons to others online. It's important to recognize these feelings and give yourself a break when things become overwhelming. Log off for awhile. Try doing something positive that makes you feel better and relieves stress, such as getting out into nature, listening to music, dancing, or practicing meditation.
Webapp.take_a_break_to_relax_1: Taking slow, deep breaths can help you feel less tension in your mind and body. Try slowly counting to 4 while you breathe in through your nose, hold that breath and count to 7, and then count to 8 as you breathe out through your mouth.
Webapp.take_a_break_to_relax_2: Focus on the here and now. An easy way to do this is name 5 things you can see, 4 things you can touch, 3 things you can hear, 2 things you can smell and 1 thing you can taste.
Webapp.take_a_break_to_relax_3: Try splashing some ice water on your face, or opening your windows to breathe in some cool fresh air. This could help calm your nervous system.
Webapp.take_a_break_to_relax_4: Journal your thoughts. If you don't know where to start, try writing it as if you’re telling someone that you trust.
Webapp.talk_to_a_professional_body: If you or someone you know is going through a difficult time, here are some resources that may help.
Webapp.talk_to_a_professional_ed: If you are struggling with an eating disorder, considering harming yourself, or if you are concerned about the well-being of a friend or family member, we strongly suggest that you seek help from a health professional or your local helpline. If the situation is an emergency, you should contact your local emergency services.
Webapp.talk_to_someone_u_trust_ed_1: If you begin to notice that you are experiencing body image or eating concerns, reach out to a family member, friend, teacher, school counselor, or someone you trust to let them know you are going through a difficult time and would like to talk about it. Remember, you don’t have to be in immediate trouble to seek support. You could share some resources about eating disorders with them ahead of time so they are prepared.
Webapp.talk_to_someone_you_trust_1: We understand that asking for help or opening up about how you are feeling can be really difficult. However, just talking to one person you trust can make you feel much better.
Webapp.talk_to_someone_you_trust_2: Let a trusted friend or family member know about what you're going through. Describe how you feel, what's happened, and what support you think might be helpful. Don’t be afraid to ask for help.
